cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents an extension of PLTL (Past Linear Temporal Logic) with atomic formulae built over a constraint system, and discusses the decidability of the satisfiability and Model Checking problem for the extended logic. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes an encoding that realizes an effective decision procedure for the Bounded Reachability problem, which is a common problem in AI. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper deals with a logic that can be used to reason about program behavior. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of the satisfiability and Model Checking problem for the extended logic, which involves algorithmic considerations. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper deals with a logic that can be used to specify and verify software systems.
